CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 3, 1966, pg. 7B reads: "Day Care At Central --- Following the program prescribed by the pastor, Rev. Isaac Green, one of the most recent innovations at Central Baptist Church, Wylie Ave. at Kirkpatrick St., is a Day Care Center, which answers a very vital need in this community. This group of bright-eyed youngsters seem to be well entertained by the efficient staff: Mrs. Francis Darby, volunteer aid, seated left; Mrs. Wanda Gilbert, standing left background, teacher-director and Mrs. Joan E. Kenley, assistant teacher.  Children between the ages of three and five are eligible to enroll.  Interested persons may contact Central Baptist Church office.-- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Twelve children, posed with staff members Joan E. Kenley, seated left, Wanda Gilbert, standing left, and Francis Darby, seated right,  in day care center in Central Baptist Church
